<F P=106> [Article by Fan Jian [5400 1696]: ``Domestic </F>
Multi-Electron-Beam Cerenkov Oscillator Experimental Research Is 
at World State-of-the-Art''] 
  [Summary] The ``8-mm multi-electron-beam Cerenkov free 
electron laser (FEL) oscillator experimental research'' project 
jointly undertaken by scientists at Beijing University's 
Technical Physics Department and at the Chinese Academy of 
Engineering Physics' Institute of Applied Electronics has 
realized an internationally unique achievement. Under the 
direction of CAS Academician Prof. Chen Jiaer [7115 0163 3167], 
physicists in the joint research group used a small accelerator 
providing 374-kV, 1.036-kA electron beams to generate a laser 
output power of 9.1 MW (at a wavelength of 8.3 mm) with an 
efficiency of 2.3 percent, an order of magnitude [i.e., 10 
times] higher than realized with similar foreign apparatuses. 

