<F P=106> [Article by Lu Jingben [4151 2417 3962] and Guan Jiabin </F>
[7070 1367 2430]: ``Superconducting Josephson-Junction-Array 
1-Volt Voltage Standard Certified''] 
  [Summary] The ``superconducting Josephson-junction-array 
1-volt voltage standard'' jointly developed by the State Bureau 
of Technology Supervision, the China Metrology Research 
Institute, and the China Testing Technology Research Institute 
recently passed formal appraisal in Beijing. The new standard 
has a measurement uncertainty of a few parts per billion, 
meeting 1990s international levels for a quantum voltage 
standard. 

