    The analysis of resources applied specifically to materials 
under the program's system (see table 2.2), shows that ceramics 
is the most seriously supported sector with total support of 
DM213.9 million, followed by polymers with DM189.4, both of 
these having more than a 20 percent share of the total for 
support. Next come the composite materials, the high-temperature 
and specialty metals [MHS] and the powder metallurgy sector. 
Projects in the corrosion and tribology sector that were 
essentially carried out in the first half of the program are 
allocated DM53.4 million (six percent of total support). 



